data.title: Succession
data.overview: The lives of the Roy family as they contemplate their future once their aging father begins to step back from the media and entertainment conglomerate they control.

seasons.title: Season 1
seasons.overview: When aging, uber-wealthy patriarch Logan Roy—CEO of one of the world's largest media and entertainment conglomerates—decides to retire, each of his four grown children follows a personal agenda that doesn't always sync with those of their siblings—or of their father.

episodes.title: Celebration
episodes.overview: On his 80th birthday, media magnate Logan Roy, whose imminent retirement was thought to be a given, shocks his family by announcing he's staying on indefinitely as CEO of Waystar/Royco. The news shatters his son Kendall, the heir apparent who's in the midst of negotiating the purchase of a digital-media venture founded by a slick operator named Lawrence.

episodes.title: Sh*t Show at the F**k Factory
episodes.overview: Logan's incapacitation sets off a heated succession debate among his children, as the Board rushes to inform the media about leadership contingencies before the stock market opens. Greg is tasked to retrieve some important items from the Roy apartment. Kendall makes an impassioned final plea to keep Waystar/Royco in the family, and receives some sobering news.

episodes.title: Lifeboats
episodes.overview: With Waystar's stock plunging to dangerous lows, Kendall is confronted with a major crisis involving a secret bank debt. Upset with Marcia for pulling rank in the Roy apartment, Shiv decides to enlist an old paramour to conduct a background check on Logan's third wife. Kendall and Roman attend their first big meeting in their new roles, as do Tom and Greg.

episodes.title: Sad Sack Wasp Trap
episodes.overview: With the company’s annual foundation gala fundraiser approaching, and his dad out of the picture, Kendall polishes up his speech while enlisting an on-air personality from the Waystar’s ATV Networks to accompany him. Shiv tries to minimize damage from a sordid photo that threatens a client's political future. Tom inherits a “virus” from his predecessor.

episodes.title: I Went to Market
episodes.overview: After hearing Logan’s plan to expand in to local TV, Kendall begins to plot a vote of no confidence against his father. Greg drives his ornery grandfather Ewan from Canada to New York for a Thanksgiving reunion with Logan. Tom grows increasingly concerned about the terms of his prenuptial agreement with Shiv, and recruits Greg for a clandestine task.

episodes.title: Which Side Are You On?
episodes.overview: With the vote of no confidence against Logan approaching, Roman attempts to sway a neutral board member, while Kendall frantically shores up his “yea” votes. Logan arrives in Washington to meet with the president, but worries he's been snubbed after a last-minute cancellation. After successfully thwarting a potential scandal, Tom introduces Greg to fine dining.

episodes.title: Austerlitz
episodes.overview: In an effort to fix his public image, Logan agrees to a family therapy session at Connor’s New Mexico ranch that Logan intends to double as a publicity stunt. While lying low, Kendall spends some time with the locals and finds his sobriety tested. Shiv considers putting herself in a precarious situation when Nate pushes her to join a potential presidential candidate’s team.

episodes.title: Prague
episodes.overview: Tom has a bachelor’s party to remember. Kendall eyes a new business opportunity with a pair of idealistic entrepreneurs. Roman looks to land a deal for local TV stations with his father’s longtime nemesis. Logan tasks Greg to act as Kendall’s babysitter during Tom’s party. Shiv and Gil get ambushed during a TV interview on a Waystar network.

episodes.title: Pre-Nuptial
episodes.overview: The Roys assemble at an English castle to prepare for Shiv and Tom’s wedding. The children reunite with their mother Caroline, who is every bit as acerbic as Logan. As guests mingle and clash, Kendall learns from Stewy and Sandy that their plot for a hostile takeover of Waystar has been fast-tracked in order to catch Logan off guard.

episodes.title: Nobody Is Ever Missing
episodes.overview: Amidst the revelry of Tom and Shiv's wedding, Logan and his team find themselves in defense mode as word of the Waystar takeover bid spreads. Kendall finds an escape outlet as the situation becomes supercharged, while Tom parlays his new wife's candor into the removal of an unwanted guest. Season One Finale.

seasons.title: Season 2
seasons.overview: Beginning where season one dramatically left off, season two follows the Roy family as they struggle to retain control of their empire, and while the future looks increasingly uncertain, it is the past that threatens to ultimately destroy them.

episodes.title: The Summer Palace
episodes.overview: Kendall tries to make amends with his dad for his takeover attempt betrayal. Logan receives some unvarnished advice from his banker about the next best move for Waystar Royco. As Tom maneuvers for a new position in the company, Shiv tries to determine whether Logan is playing mind games regarding his successor.

episodes.title: Vaulter
episodes.overview: Roman and Kendall do a “routine health check” of a new media brand to help Vaulter to determine the future of the company. Tom tasks Greg with sniffing out waste at ATN, as Greg wonders if the divisive media outlet is the right fit for him. Connor and Willa host a soiree to mark their return to New York. Shiv brings Tom in the loop about her future at Waystar and with Gil’s campaign.

episodes.title: Hunting
episodes.overview: Logan informs his management team of his plan to make another attempt to acquire a rival media company. Greg worries his meeting with a Logan biographer puts his standing with the family at risk. Connor's presidential announcement irritates Logan.

episodes.title: Safe Room
episodes.overview: Roman begins a six-week management training program. Connor and Willa attend the funeral of a family friend with a complicated past. Logan and Kendall arrange a covert meeting with PGM CEO Rhea Jarrell. Controversy surrounds a star anchor.

episodes.title: Tern Haven
episodes.overview: Logan attempts to solidify his buyout of PGM at a weekend retreat at the Pierce family home, where Shiv, Roman and Connor veer from their carefully orchestrated roles. As the Pierces question whether an alliance with Waystar Royco will tarnish their legacy, Kendall makes his case to Naomi Pierce during a drug-filled night.

episodes.title: Argestes
episodes.overview: As Logan looks to finalize a deal to buy the Pierce family's papers and TV stations at a media & banking retreat, a threat to the deal arises from an unexpected quarter. Tom worries about ATN's new slogan after learning some distressing news from Greg. Kendall, Shiv and Roman fail to see eye to eye on how to handle damage control ahead of a panel featuring the Roys.

episodes.title: Return
episodes.overview: The Roys head to the UK, where Roman and Shiv try to strike a deal with their mother and Logan and Kendall face the consequences of their last visit.

episodes.title: Dundee
episodes.overview: The entire Roy clan travels to Logan's hometown of Dundee, Scotland, for a celebration of Logan's 50 years in the business. Kendall becomes enamored with Jennifer, an actress in Willa's play. A former employee proves difficult to silence.

episodes.title: DC
episodes.overview: Logan, Kendall, Gerri and Tom testify before Congress. Shiv speaks candidly to Kira, a victim who is set to be a key witness. In Turkey, Roman's business pitch takes a chilling turn.

episodes.title: This Is Not for Tears
episodes.overview: Logan weighs whether a member of the family, or a top lieutenant, will need to be sacrificed to salvage the company's tarnished reputation. Roman shares his hesitations about a new source of financing, as Kendall suggests a familiar alternative. Season Two Finale.

seasons.title: Season 3
seasons.overview: Ambushed by his rebellious son Kendall at the end of Season 2, Logan Roy begins Season 3 in a perilous position. Scrambling to secure familial, political, and financial alliances, tensions rise as a bitter corporate battle threatens to turn into a family civil war.

episodes.title: Secession
episodes.overview: Following his bombshell presser, a righteous Kendall scrambles to find a base of operations, while Logan's team searches for safe harbor.

episodes.title: Mass in Time of War
episodes.overview: Kendall tries to get his siblings, as well as Stewy and Sandi, on his side. Fearing his legal situation, Greg asks Ewan for help.

episodes.title: The Disruption
episodes.overview: With the DOJ at the door, Logan summons his arsenal, while Tom makes a potentially life changing offer. Kendall becomes obsessed with his own takedown.

episodes.title: Lion in the Meadow
episodes.overview: Logan and Kendall have their first meeting together with Josh, a major investor worried about their family feud.

episodes.title: Retired Janitors of Idaho
episodes.overview: Kendall and the Waystar team find themselves working together at the annual shareholders’ meeting, where Logan’s health takes a turn.

episodes.title: What It Takes
episodes.overview: Logan and team head to Virginia for a conservative political conference, where Roman finds out surprising news about his mother.

episodes.title: Too Much Birthday
episodes.overview: At Kendall’s lavish birthday bash, Shiv and Roman try to arrange a meeting with Lukas Matsson, a tech mogul who recently snubbed Logan.

episodes.title: Chiantishire
episodes.overview: At a luxe family wedding in Italy, Roman airs suspicions, Gerri draws a line, and the Waystar team grows concerned about rogue tweets.

episodes.title: All the Bells Say
episodes.overview: Matsson’s vision for the GoJo-Waystar relationship leads Shiv and Roman to manage the fallout, while Logan weighs his options.

seasons.title: Season 4
seasons.overview: In season four, the sale of media conglomerate Waystar Royco to tech visionary Lukas Matsson moves ever closer. The prospect of this seismic sale provokes existential angst and familial division among the Roys as they anticipate what their lives will look like once the deal is completed. A power struggle ensues as the family weighs up a future where their cultural and political weight is severely curtailed.

episodes.title: If He Had a Hundred Years

data.title: Inheritance
data.overview: The patriarch of a wealthy and powerful family suddenly passes away, leaving his wife and daughter with a shocking secret inheritance that threatens to unravel and destroy their lives.

data.title: 2001: A Space Odyssey
data.overview: Humanity finds a mysterious object buried beneath the lunar surface and sets off to find its origins with the help of HAL 9000, the world's most advanced super computer.

data.title: Better Call Saul
data.overview: Six years before Saul Goodman meets Walter White. We meet him when the man who will become Saul Goodman is known as Jimmy McGill, a small-time lawyer searching for his destiny, and, more immediately, hustling to make ends meet. Working alongside, and, often, against Jimmy, is “fixer” Mike Ehrmantraut. The series tracks Jimmy’s transformation into Saul Goodman, the man who puts “criminal” in “criminal lawyer".

seasons.title: Season 1
seasons.overview: When we meet him, the man who will become Saul Goodman is known as Jimmy McGill, a small-time lawyer searching for his destiny, and, more immediately, hustling to make ends meet. Working alongside, and often against, Jimmy is “fixer” Mike Erhmantraut.

episodes.title: Uno
episodes.overview: Jimmy works his magic in the courtroom. Unexpected inspiration leads him to an unconventional pursuit of potential clients.

episodes.title: Mijo
episodes.overview: As his troubles escalate to a boiling point, Jimmy finds himself in dire straits. An act of carelessness puts Chuck at risk.

episodes.title: Nacho
episodes.overview: Jimmy pulls out all the stops to prove that his dangerous client is innocent, even though it causes some friction with Kim.

episodes.title: Hero
episodes.overview: Jimmy devises a bold plan to obtain new clients, but must face consequences when his relationships become strained.

episodes.title: Alpine Shepherd Boy
episodes.overview: Alarming news disrupts Jimmy's efforts at drumming up new business, forcing him to make a difficult choice.

episodes.title: Five-O
episodes.overview: Mike's tragic past comes back to haunt him, and he's forced to seek help from an unusual source. Jimmy's moral compass is put to the test.

episodes.title: Bingo
episodes.overview: Jimmy meets with potential new clients. Then, when given the opportunity to do the right thing, he cashes in a favor from an unlikely ally.

episodes.title: RICO
episodes.overview: Jimmy shows Chuck that he's willing to do almost anything to win a case, even if it means getting his hands dirty.

episodes.title: Pimento
episodes.overview: Chuck urges Jimmy to accept a harsh truth. Meanwhile, a deal threatens to go off the rails when Mike's ability to complete a job is called into question.

episodes.title: Marco
episodes.overview: In the aftermath of recent events, Jimmy seizes an opportunity to reconnect with an old friend. Chuck adjusts to a new way of life.

seasons.title: Season 2
seasons.overview: Season one left Jimmy at the center of a large class-action lawsuit that led to a promising job opportunity at a prestigious firm in Santa Fe. Having arrived at a fork in the road, will Jimmy take the straight and narrow path with a safe corporate job or will he fall back into his “Slippin’ Jimmy” con artist ways?

episodes.title: Switch
episodes.overview: Jimmy and Kim's relationship takes a new turn. Mike decides it's for the best to sever his affiliation with an unrestrained associate.

episodes.title: Cobbler
episodes.overview: To keep a potentially messy situation from unraveling, Mike brokers a deal. Jimmy works to exonerate an eccentric client.

episodes.title: Amarillo
episodes.overview: Jimmy's client outreach efforts thrive, and he exhibits new heights of showmanship. Mike is perplexed by daughter-in-law Stacey's troubling news.

episodes.title: Gloves Off
episodes.overview: Jimmy's actions unexpectedly create waves for Kim. Mike cautiously weighs a lucrative proposal that might bring about dire consequences.

episodes.title: Rebecca
episodes.overview: Jimmy becomes frustrated with his restrictive work environment. Kim pulls out all the stops to dig herself out of a seemingly bottomless hole at HHM.

episodes.title: Bali Ha'i
episodes.overview: Jimmy finds comfort in familiarity. Kim receives a life-changing proposal. When he is threatened, Mike finds himself pushed to the limit.

episodes.title: Inflatable
episodes.overview: Mike's growing frustration shows when his hand is forced, but with Jimmy's help, he works to keep the peace. Meanwhile, Jimmy boldly forges a new path forward.

episodes.title: Fifi
episodes.overview: Mike aims to settle the score with an enemy; an unexpected opportunity presents itself to Jimmy.

episodes.title: Nailed
episodes.overview: Mike takes a methodical approach to his mission. Someone questions Chuck's capabilities. Jimmy faces a personal dilemma.

episodes.title: Klick
episodes.overview: Jimmy must make a hard choice. Mike takes control of matters. Hamlin delivers shocking news.

seasons.title: Season 3
seasons.overview: As the season three begins, the repercussions of Chuck's scheme test Jimmy and Kim's fledgling law practices -- and their romance -- as never before. This imminent existential threat presses Jimmy’s faltering moral compass to the limit. Meanwhile, Mike searches for a mysterious adversary who seems to know almost everything about his business.

episodes.title: Mabel
episodes.overview: Jimmy and Chuck's relationship deteriorates. Kim feels the pressure of running her own firm. Mike investigates the note left on his car.

episodes.title: Witness
episodes.overview: Jimmy and Kim hire an assistant. Mike seeks out a mysterious acquaintance. Chuck uses the law to gain an advantage over Jimmy.

episodes.title: Sunk Costs
episodes.overview: Jimmy decides to represent a new client to Kim's dismay. Mike meets a formidable ally who gives a tempting offer.

episodes.title: Sabrosito
episodes.overview: Jimmy asks a favor of Mike; new complications disrupt Salamancas' business. Chuck and Jimmy struggle with a compromise.

episodes.title: Chicanery
episodes.overview: Kim and Jimmy face off with an adversary. Jimmy looks to Chuck's past to secure his future. Jimmy loses an ally and gains another.

episodes.title: Off Brand
episodes.overview: Jimmy has a new endeavor. Chuck pushes himself to the limit. Nacho finds himself in a power struggle.

episodes.title: Expenses
episodes.overview: Jimmy tries to settle debts. Nacho reunites with an acquaintance. Mike helps Stacey with a project and makes a connection.

episodes.title: Slip
episodes.overview: Jimmy is pushed to desperate measures. Nacho picks up a new skill. Mike explores an alliance. Kim stands up to Hamlin.

episodes.title: Fall
episodes.overview: Jimmy visits an old friend and takes up a new pastime. Chuck and Hamlin spar over the future of the firm. Kim faces challenges at work.

episodes.title: Lantern
episodes.overview: Kim takes time off. Jimmy tries to make amends. Nacho gambles with his future. Hamlin pushes Chuck to make a decision.

seasons.title: Season 4
seasons.overview: In Season 4, in the wake of a loss, Jimmy takes steps into the criminal world that will put his future as a lawyer — and his relationship with Kim — in jeopardy.

episodes.title: Smoke
episodes.overview: Jimmy struggles to cope with Chuck's tragic death. Mike ponders his role at Madrigal. Howard makes a startling confession.

episodes.title: Breathe
episodes.overview: Jimmy seeks new employment. Gus navigates the fallout from Hector's collapse. Kim endeavors to support Jimmy in the wake of Chuck's death.

episodes.title: Something Beautiful
episodes.overview: Jimmy puts a risky plan into motion. As alliances shift, Nacho finds himself in the crosshairs. Kim contemplates her future.

episodes.title: Talk
episodes.overview: A restless Jimmy embarks on a new endeavor while Mike burns bridges. Kim pursues her bliss. Nacho tries to survive a turf war.

episodes.title: Quite a Ride
episodes.overview: Jimmy identifies a new market for his talents. Mike vets a potential partnership. Kim drives a hard bargain.

episodes.title: Piñata
episodes.overview: While Jimmy dreams of Wexler-McGill, Kim makes a bold move. Mike puts a plan into motion for Gus.

episodes.title: Something Stupid
episodes.overview: Jimmy expands his business, but runs into a problem that only Kim can solve. Gus intervenes in Hector's medical care. Mike deals with a setback.

episodes.title: Coushatta
episodes.overview: Jimmy goes to great lengths to right a wrong, as Kim pulls out all the stops for a case. Mike lets his team blow off steam. Nacho receives a visitor.

episodes.title: Wiedersehen
episodes.overview: Jimmy and Kim unburden themselves, risking their relationship in the process. Nacho is forced to make the rounds with Lalo. Mike has cause to worry.

episodes.title: Winner
episodes.overview: Jimmy turns the page on his reputation. Lalo tracks a loose end in Gus' operation. Mike is forced to make a difficult decision.

seasons.title: Season 5
seasons.overview: Jimmy finally makes the decision that changes everything — to practice law as “Saul Goodman.” And this decision will soon create unexpected and profound waves of change for everyone in his world.

episodes.title: Magic Man
episodes.overview: Now doing business as Saul Goodman, Jimmy unveils an unorthodox strategy for client development that tests Kim's tolerance of his new legal persona. Lalo searches for the mysterious Michael, only to discover a problem within his own operation.

episodes.title: 50% Off
episodes.overview: Jimmy's promotional stunt has unintended consequences. Nacho takes extreme measures to earn Lalo's trust. Saul is a success at the courthouse but still has yet to win Kim over. Simmering with rage and self-loathing, Mike loses his temper.

episodes.title: The Guy for This
episodes.overview: Jimmy's business enters uncharted territory. Kim's confidence is tested when she's faced with a legal problem only she can solve. Nacho navigates increased pressure from Gus. Mike continues to spiral.

episodes.title: Namaste
episodes.overview: As Jimmy doubles down on Saul Goodman, a deeply conflicted Kim brings him an interesting proposition, Gus makes a sacrifice in order to play the long game, and Mike attempts to smooth things over with his family.

episodes.title: Dedicado a Max
episodes.overview: Mike takes an impromptu trip out of town. As she and Jimmy grow closer over their campaign to help a client, Kim makes a surprising call.

episodes.title: Wexler v. Goodman
episodes.overview: Kim tries to pump the brakes on Jimmy's latest scheme, but it may be too late to stop Saul. Mike turns the heat up on Lalo. Nacho attempts to enlist support from above.

episodes.title: JMM
episodes.overview: Jimmy and Kim build a legal firewall with help from Huell. Kim sets things straight with her clients as Jimmy is compromised by his. Gus, at war on all fronts, calms troubled waters in service of his plot to build an empire. Mike does damage control.

episodes.title: Bagman
episodes.overview: When a simple errand for a client goes sideways, Jimmy is pushed to the limit. Mike takes measures to contain the wrath of the cartel. Lalo gets an unexpected visitor.

episodes.title: Bad Choice Road
episodes.overview: In the wake of Jimmy's traumatic misadventure, Kim takes stock of what is important. Jimmy attempts to return to business as usual, but it's more difficult than anticipated. Gus and Mike set a plan in motion.

episodes.title: Something Unforgivable
episodes.overview: Jimmy and Kim make a sideways move that takes a serious turn. Nacho gets closer to the cartel than he'd like. Season Finale.

seasons.title: Season 6
seasons.overview: The final season concludes the complicated journey and transformation of its compromised hero, Jimmy McGill, into criminal lawyer Saul Goodman. From the cartel to the courthouse, from Albuquerque to Omaha, season six tracks Jimmy, Saul and Gene as well as Jimmy’s complex relationship with Kim, who is in the midst of her own existential crisis. Meanwhile, Mike, Gus, Nacho and Lalo are locked into a game of cat and mouse with mortal stakes.

episodes.title: Wine and Roses
episodes.overview: Nacho runs for his life. Jimmy and Kim hatch a plan. Mike questions his allegiances.

episodes.title: Carrot and Stick
episodes.overview: Harsh realities dawn on Nacho. Gus investigates his suspicions.

episodes.title: Rock and Hard Place
episodes.overview: Still on the run, Nacho is forced to choose where his loyalties lie. Jimmy doubles down.

episodes.title: Hit and Run
episodes.overview: Gus takes extreme measures. Jimmy and Kim enlist a local pro to put on a show.

episodes.title: Black and Blue
episodes.overview: While business booms for Jimmy, the vise tightens on the cat-and-mouse game between Gus and Lalo.

episodes.title: Axe and Grind
episodes.overview: Kim and Jimmy enlist a knowledgeable contact. Howard scrutinizes Jimmy’s business practices.

episodes.title: Plan and Execution
episodes.overview: Jimmy and Kim deal with a last-minute snag. Howard's investigation finally yields results.

episodes.title: Point and Shoot
episodes.overview: An unexpected visitor forces Jimmy and Kim to face the consequences of their actions.

episodes.title: Fun and Games
episodes.overview: Gus attempts to smooth things over with the cartel while Mike ties up loose ends.

episodes.title: Nippy
episodes.overview: A lost dog leads to a new friend. A new player gets in the game.

episodes.title: Breaking Bad
episodes.overview: Emboldened by recent successes, partners throw caution to the wind and escalate their enterprise to new levels.

episodes.title: Waterworks
episodes.overview: The stakes are raised when a discovery is made that will send shockwaves far and wide.

episodes.title: Saul Gone
episodes.overview: The series finale.
